data:
"Take part in Europe" is the EVS project of YEPP. Participation on the European level is one of our the basic values. We feel that hosting an EVS volunteer in the office strengthens this position and shows that we don't only 'talk the talk', but also 'walk the walk'. With this project we want to:
- Stimulate active participation in Europe;
- contribute to European policy making by bringing real life stories to policy makers;
- provide a learning space for the volunteer;
- enrich and broaden the work of the organisation.

The EVS project will last 12 months. The volunteer will be involved in organizing and implementing the 5 YEPP conferences. S/he will also support the communication between YEPP and its 60 Member Organisations as well as being involved in supporting the administration of the organisation with a focus on finances of projects and fundraising. To make sure the dissemination of the service is assured, the volunteer will support the campaigns of YEPP based on the recommendations that came out of the conferences. Of course, the volunteer will be involved in the political work of the organization. Concretely this means: editing policy papers, coordinating policy papers and campaigns with different stakeholders. In addition, we want to make sure that the volunteer has sufficient time to develop and implement a personal project with support of YEPP. The volunteer is free to chose this project but obviously it should be in line with the values and the work of YEPP. This project will help the volunteer to develop self directed learning skills. The volunteer also has the chance to take part in language classes so s/he can integrate more easily in the local community.
